Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box in Page 03
And	I go to Page 07 of Elbow MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Soft tissue tumor' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' or 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Subcutaneous' checkbox is enabled
And 'No displacement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Along the tendon sheath' checkbox is enabled
And 'Along median nerve' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration' checkbox is enabled

And 'Cutis thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pressure erosion/bony erosion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Macrodactyly' checkbox is enabled


And 'Signal T1w' slide bar is enabled
And 'Signal T2w' slide bar is enabled

And 'No' radio button is enabled
And 'Mild' radio button is enabled
And 'Strong' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Mild' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
